<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNOCAL SPILLAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "UNOCAL Admits Spillage Into Ocean; Guilty Plea Expected," March 12: 
</P>
<P>
 A youth found with some pot in his possession (hurting no one but himself, if 
at all) winds up in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 UNOCAL confesses to polluting leakage spilling into the ocean for the last 15 
years, 8.5 million gallons of diluent, and is settling a 36-count criminal 
complaint for three misdemeanors and a fine of $1.5 million, a pittance for 
UNOCAL, and of course, no jail time for these white-collar criminals who have 
known they were polluting our environment. 
</P>
<P>
 Is this fair? And don't tell me about apples and oranges. 
</P>
<P>
 MILDRED HASSAN 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
