<TEXT>
<P>
 Arthur Nestor Hews, 68, a nationally known personal injury attorney and more 
recently chief executive officer of the Los Angeles-based Wave Newspaper Group. 
Hews became CEO of Wave Newspapers in 1988.He helped merge Wave with Urban 
Newspapers this month and was named CEO of the combined company, the Wave 
Newspaper Group. The groups publish more than 600,000 papers and distribute 
them in South-Central Los Angeles and southeast Los Angeles County. Among Hews' 
better known legal cases was a $128-million award to his clients in 1970 from 
the Ford Motor Co. for liability resulting from the fiery crash of a defective 
