<P>
 The Exchange Club Child Abuse Prevention Center of Costa Mesa is seeking 
Spanish-speaking volunteers to work in its new parent-aide program. 
</P>
<P>
 The volunteer aides are needed to help families where an incident of child 
abuse has occurred or is at risk of occurring, center officials said. The goal 
is for the volunteer and the parents to develop a trusting relationship that 
can help solve domestic problems. 
