<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; VOLUNTEERS WITH BACK PAIN SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Palma Intercommunity Hospital's physical therapy department is looking for 
volunteers with low back pain to participate in a training course for physical 
therapists. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with pain, burning, tingling or numbness in the back or legs will 
receive an extensive evaluation and up to four days of free treatment. 
</P>
<P>
 In cooperation with the McKenzie Institute USA, the hospital is making the 
offer to teach physical therapists about specialized evaluation and treatment 
of low back problems. 
</P>
<P>
 The course will be held April 7 to 10 at La Palma Intercommunity Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in participating as a patient can call (714) 670-6209. 
</P>
