<DOCID> 026963 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 28, 1994, Monday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 4; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
168 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISPUTE OVER DEBT LEADS TO SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 29-year-old man was shot to death outside his apartment Sunday morning 
during an argument with another man who owed him money, Los Angeles police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Napoleon Orellana was pronounced dead outside 6740 Hayvenhurst Ave. near 
the Van Nuys Airport, said Detective Dan O'Hanian of the Los Angeles Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Police issued an alert for the gray 1990 Toyota pickup truck that the suspect, 
Hector Rodolfo Mejia, used to flee the scene. The truck has a California 
license plate number, 3Z82354. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities believe that Mejia, 36, lived on and off at the apartment complex 
and was staying there Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mejia owed Orellana money, O'Hanian said, and the two men had apparently been 
arguing over it for several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 About 7:30 a.m. Sunday, Mejia allegedly shot Orellana with a handgun several 
times in the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
 The killing is the second homicide of the year in the Van Nuys Division, 
O'Hanian said. 
</P>
<P>
 Orellana is survived by his wife, Carmen Ramos, and a 10-month-old daughter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
