</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; PIPE BOMB BLAST DAMAGES RV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No one was injured when a pipe bomb exploded beneath a recreational vehicle 
parked behind a Sierra Highway cafe, sheriff's deputies said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies said they have no suspects and no motive in the case. 
</P>
<P>
 Rini Duzanne, 51, the vehicle's owner, said that upon returning to her home 
about 7:45 p.m. Saturday she noticed that her rear left tires were flat and 
that the rear cabin of her vehicle had sunk to the ground. Inside, the bathroom 
toilet and shower were damaged, Duzanne said. She thought that the motor home 
had sunk because of the flattened tires. 
</P>
<P>
 The next morning, Duzanne noticed that her tires were not flattened but blown 
apart, and after seeing metal fragments underneath and around her vehicle she 
notified police. 
</P>
<P>
 An arson investigation team determined that a pipe bomb had caused the damage, 
estimated at $5,000. 
</P>
