<HEADLINE>
<P>
ECONOMIC PROFILE DEBUTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Edition today begins a new feature on B2 that will give 
timely information to readers interested in the economic pulse of our 
communities. 
</P>
<P>
 In cooperation with the Economic Forecast Project at UC Santa Barbara, The 
Times each Monday will print an economic profile that will list all the latest 
available numbers about everything from employment to home sales to building 
permits. 
</P>
<P>
 Not all the numbers change each week, but they are updated by the Economic 
Forecast Project as soon as they are available to give Times readers a quick 
reference chart. 
</P>
</TEXT>
