<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; SCHOOL TO REOPEN, GET NEW PRINCIPAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gerry Aust has been appointed principal of the C.E. Utt Middle School, which 
will reopen this fall at its original campus on Browning Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustees of Tustin Unified School District named Aust, currently principal of 
Marjorie Veeh Elementary School, to his new job earlier this month.He has been 
with the school district for 31 years. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials said that Utt Middle School, which was closed in 1978 
because of declining enrollment, was reopened because of the increasing number 
of students entering sixth, seventh and eighth grades. 
</P>
<P>
 With the school's reopening, the district will have three middle schools. The 
others are A.G. Currie and Columbus Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
 Columbus Tustin, which has been using the Utt campus for the last three years, 
will return to its former site at 17952 Beneta Way in September, district 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Beneta Way campus was closed in 1991 for renovation. Bob Boies will remain 
the school principal. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
