WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; FIRES AT HOUSE, PARK UNDER INVESTIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura city fire officials Sunday were investigating two suspicious blazes 
that broke out within an hour of each other in a Ventura Avenue neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents in the 100 block of East Simpson Avenue reported a house fire about 
1:30 a.m. Sunday; the home was fully engulfed when fire crews arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 Emergency crews were able to extinguish the fire within 20 minutes, but the 
structure at 128 E. Simpson Ave. suffered $50,000 in damage, and the family 
lost possessions worth $5,000, fire investigators said. A neighboring house had 
paint damage. 
</P>
<P>
 A second fire was reported about 45 minutes later at the Westpark Recreation 
Center, a facility in the 400 block of West Harrison Avenue, about four blocks 
from the first blaze. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators estimated damage to the park facility at $250. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in either fire. Investigators said both are still under 
investigation. JEFF McDONALD 
