<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Autos and Parts to Be Promoted: The Japan Auto Parts Industries Assn. and 
the Japan Automobile Importers Assn., following the example of the Japan 
Automobile Manufacturers Assn., announced plans to promote U.S. autos and auto 
parts.Automobiles and components account for roughly two-thirds of Japan's 
$59-billion trade surplus with the United States. The plan released by the 
Japan Auto Parts Industries Assn., which represents 529 Japanese component 
manufacturers, proposed regular meetings with U.S. auto parts makers to expand 
business opportunities. The Japan Automobile Importers Assn. said it will 
increase the number of import exhibits it holds. The association will also 
