<P>
FIVE COMPOSERS SCORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PASLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five composers from Orange County are among 18 selected from throughout the 
state for the first "Voces Novae" festival, to be held April 14 through 16 at 
Cal State Fullerton. The 18 were selected from a field of 43 by CSUF faculty 
members Lloyd Rodgers and Michael Bayer. 
</P>
<P>
 Prelude No. 4 by Tom Liddell of Placentia and "Pierre" by Olivia Herman of 
Irvine will be played April 14. Quartet in G by Charles Gran of Huntington 
Beach and String Quartet No. 2 by Randy McRill of Fullerton will be played 
April 15, and "Scardanelli Songs" by Paul Greenhaw of Fullerton will be played 
April 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Each concert will begin at 8 p.m. Tickets will cost $8 ($5 for Cal State 
Fullerton students). Information: (714) 773-3371. CHRIS PASLES 
