<P>
DELIA, TITANS WIN BIG WEST TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton's Celeste Delia won the overall title at the Big West 
Conference women's gymnastics championships, leading the Titans to the team 
title Sunday at the Events Center in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans won the team title with 190.50 points. Utah State (190.45) was 
second and UC Santa Barbara (189.05) third. 
</P>
<P>
 The overall victory for Delia, a senior from Covina Northview High School, was 
her third consecutive. She was also selected the Big West Conference's gymnast 
of the year for the third year in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, the Titans advance to Western regional as the No. 3-seeded 
team. The regional is April 9 at Boise State. 
