<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORKUM INJURED, OUT FOR SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mighty Ducks have lost leading scorer Bob Corkum for the rest of the 
season after a skate blade cut a tendon in his right foot Sunday during the 
third period of the team's game against Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
 General Manager Jack Ferreira said Corkum will probably undergo surgery today 
to repair the tendon on top of his foot near the ankle. The examining doctor 
said the tendon is at least 75% severed. 
</P>
<P>
 Corkum, 26, had never scored more than 10 points in an NHL season before this 
year, but he scored his 51st point with an assist Sunday before being hurt. 
ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
